net.hudup.core.alg

Class ExecutableAlgRemoteWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.AlgRemoteWrapper
      • net.hudup.core.alg.ExecutableAlgRemoteWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote, java.util.EventListener, Alg, AlgRemote, AlgRemoteTask, ExecutableAlg, ExecutableAlgRemote, ExecutableAlgRemoteTask, SetupAlgListener, Exportable, Inspectable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AugRemoteWrapper

    @BaseClass
public class ExecutableAlgRemoteWrapper
extends AlgRemoteWrapper
implements ExecutableAlg, ExecutableAlgRemote
    The class is a wrapper of remote executable algorithm. This is a trick to use RMI object but not to break the defined programming architecture. In fact, RMI mechanism has some troubles or it it affect negatively good architecture. For usage, an algorithm as REM will has a pair: REM stub (remote executable algorithm) and REM wrapper (normal executable algorithm). The server creates REM stub (remote executable algorithm) and the client creates and uses the REM wrapper as normal executable algorithm.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
